-- Migration 0053: reach 68 (aw_4023) NF Rogue — rename + put-in + snap
--
-- Operator review of the gradient profile chart surfaced reach 68 in
-- the >= 1000 ft/mi extreme-peak triage list (post-0052 cohort). Three
-- changes combine here:
--
-- 1. Metadata cleanup: display_name was "Mill Creek to Lost Creek Resv"
--    (which is actually the section description). Move that string to
--    the description column and set display_name to "NF Rogue", matching
--    the rest of the NF Rogue catalog.
--
-- 2. Put-in adjusted ~7 m to operator-supplied coord
--    (42.7400279186052, -122.49582603895693). Tiny offset but enough to
--    drop the headline peak from 1024 -> 988 ft/mi (just below the
--    extreme-peak threshold).
--
-- 3. Apply scripts/snap_reach_to_channel_min.py (perpendicular-min
--    channel snap) since this is a deep forested gorge where the NHD-HR
--    trace can route through canopy / canyon walls. 30 of 119 vertices
--    snapped, mean drop 13.4 ft, mean offset 13.3 m. Profile peak then
--    drops to 579 ft/mi; max_gradient 214 -> 203 ft/mi.
--
-- Reach is 100% 1arc3-sourced (no OPR LIDAR coverage in this section
-- of the Rogue headwaters) — the snap is working on 10 m 3DEP cells.
--
-- Idempotent: aw_id + display_name check guard.

